Self Driving Auto-Labeler

This is a custom auto-labeling stack utilizing deep learning (segmentation), visual odometry, sensor data and Kalman filter to generate a path and road edges
It uses data from Carla autonomous driving simulator

Sensors to extract data from:
- Gyroscope/IMU
- GPS/GNSS
- camera => visual odometry
- steering wheel angle sensor

Libraries to use:
- Laika for GNSS
- Rednose for Kalman
- SegNet for segmentation


